article.headline: Navy 67, Army 62 (OT)
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Greg Sprink hit a 3-pointer at the end of regulation and then scored five points in overtime to give Navy a 67-62 victory over Army on Sunday. Sprink finished with 23 points for the Middies (9-13, 2-6 Patriot League). Matt Bell had 18 points for Army (5-16, 1-8), while Jarell Brown added 15. There were 14 ties and 18 lead changes in the game. Matt Fannin scored in the lane with 34 seconds left to give Navy the lead for good, 63-62. Sprink and Corey Johnson each added two free throws for the final margin.
